<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 13 at 6:36PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of eastern Texas,
Beaver, western Lipscomb, southeastern Randall, Gray, southeastern
Hansford, Roberts, Ochiltree, Armstrong, northwestern Wheeler,
eastern Carson, eastern Hutchinson, western Hemphill and northwestern
Donley Counties through 730 PM CDT...
At 635 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 5 miles northeast of Baker to 5 miles southwest
of Bryans Corner to 14 miles southeast of Waka to 9 miles north of
Pampa to 7 miles west of Groom to 5 miles east of Happy. Movement was
east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.  Blowing dust may reduce visibility
below 1 mile at times.
Locations impacted include...
Pampa, Perryton, Canadian, Beaver, Claude, Miami, Booker, White Deer,
Groom, Forgan, Lefors, Skellytown, Howardwick, Darrouzett, Wolf Creek
Park, Lake Mcclellan, Wayside, Goodnight, Baker and Kingsmill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
